<%# Profile header: a light "← My Pets" kicker, then the pet name, then a tab row
    that carries the section nav on the left and a de-emphasized "Delete pet"
    action on the right, all sitting on a hairline divider. The avatar lives in
    the About Identity card; per-section add/edit actions live in each tab.
    Renders above EVERY tab (via _profile_shell), so it's the home for pet-level
    actions like delete. %>
<%# turbo_frame: "_top" breaks out of the pet_content frame to navigate the whole
    page back to the roster. %>
<%= link_to pets_path, class: "back-link text-secondary text-decoration-none small fw-medium d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2 mb-2", data: { turbo_frame: "_top" } do %>
  <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left"></i>
  My Pets
<% end %>

<div class="mb-4">
  <%# Pet name only — species/breed/age live in the Identity card. The id lets
      update.turbo_stream.erb refresh just this name after an edit. %>
  <h1 id="<%= dom_id(pet, :pet_name) %>" class="fw-bold mb-3 text-ink text-truncate"><%= pet.name %></h1>

  <%# Tab row: nav on the left, Delete pushed right (ms-auto), aligned to their
      bottoms so both sit on the divider. Keeps pb-2 + a bottom border so the
      active .pet-tab underline lands cleanly on it (its negative margin is tuned
      to this pb-2). gap-3 keeps the button off the tabs when they get wide. %>
  <div class="d-flex align-items-end gap-3 border-bottom border-secondary-subtle pb-2">
    <div class="flex-grow-1" style="min-width: 0;">
      <%= render "pets/nav_tabs", pet: pet, active_tab: active_tab %>
    </div>
    <%# Delete the ENTIRE pet: a de-emphasized trigger that loads a styled
        confirmation into the shared modal (drawer frame) rather than the
        browser's native confirm(). The real, filled Delete button lives inside
        that confirmation (see pets/confirm_delete). %>
    <%= link_to confirm_delete_pet_path(pet),
          class: "btn btn-sm btn-outline-danger rounded-pill flex-shrink-0 d-inline-flex align-items-center gap-2",
          data: { turbo_frame: "drawer" } do %>
      <i class="fa-regular fa-trash-can"></i>
      <span class="d-none d-sm-inline">Delete pet</span>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
